The Grade 7 pupil, who died on Thursday, tested negative for COVID-19. This has been revealed by the Gauteng health department. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - It is still unknown what caused the death of a 12-year-old pupil at Kokosi Primary School in Fochville. READ: Benefits for children going back to school outweigh risks: expert The Grade 7 pupil, who died on Thursday, tested negative for COVID-19. This has been revealed by the Gauteng health department. Ben Thokozani Thafeni was not feeling well at school, his temperature was checked and he was put in isolation. He was rushed to a nearby clinic but was certified dead on arrival. The Education Department and the province's health department have launched an investigation into the incident. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.